-- Iceland bourse says to remain closed on Monday
-- 
-- Mon Oct 13, 2008 2:30pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/10/13/us-iceland-stocks-idUSTRE49C2YE20081013

 

 STOCKHOLM  (Reuters) - The Icelandic stock exchange said share trading would remain suspended on Monday due to "unusual market conditions," but that equity markets would reopen on Tuesday. The stock market in the crisis-hit North Atlantic island nation has been closed since last Thursday. 

